cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it presents a new framework for managing resources in software-defined networks. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses mechanisms for verifying modifications made to sub-policies do not violate global constraints. Additionally, it may belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it presents a language for expressing network policies and a compiler for translating them into code. Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the scalability of the framework on real-world topologies and applications.
